AU  - Gomes, Francisco J.
AU  - Maenhout, Pascal J.
T1  - Consumption and Portfolio Choice over the Life Cycle
PY  - 2005
Y1  - 2005/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhi017
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 18
IS  - 2
SP  - 491
EP  - 533
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This article solves a realistically calibrated life cycle model of consumption and portfolio choice with non-tradable labor income and borrowing constraints. Since labor income substitutes for riskless asset holdings, the optimal share invested in equities is roughly decreasing over life. We compute a measure of the importance of human capital for investment behavior. We find that ignoring labor income generates large utility costs, while the cost of ignoring only its risk is an order of magnitude smaller, except when we allow for a disastrous labor income shock. Moreover, we study the implications of introducing endogenous borrowing constraints in this incomplete-markets setting.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhi017
ER  - 



